Remove NULL Invoices
Invoices should never be null for valid transactions.
# Remove rows where Invoice is missing
df = df[df['Invoice'].notna()]

Remove Canceled Orders.
Canceled orders in this dataset are identified by Invoice numbers starting with C.
# Remove canceled invoices
df = df[~df['Invoice'].astype(str).str.startswith('C')]

Remove Rows with Missing Customer ID (Important for RFM)
df = df[df['Customer ID'].notna()]

Remove Invalid Quantities & Prices
Negative or zero values are not meaningful for sales analysis.
df = df[(df['Quantity'] > 0) & (df['Price'] > 0)]

Convert Invoice Date to Datetime
df['InvoiceDate'] = pd.to_datetime(df['InvoiceDate'])

